A narrow slit of sunlight breaks across the bedsheet as the first rays of sunlight dip into the room.  The intrusion lands squarely upon the face of a man whom lies precariously asleep. 

&lt;&lt;click &quot;What does the room look like?&quot;&gt;&gt;&lt;&lt;toggleclass &quot;#protagonistRoomDesc&quot; &quot;hidden&quot;&gt;&gt;&lt;&lt;/click&gt;&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;protagonistRoomDesc&quot; class=&quot;hidden&quot;&gt;If there is one word to describe the conditions in which the man lived it would be oblong.  It takes the shape of a narrow pill, with the door at one end and the man&#39;s bed at the other.  The room was about twenty paces long but the width of the space was the dimension of a queen-sized bed, which is what the man lies on now.  Due to this fact, there is no room for an end table on either side of the bed.  In fact, the only other furniture to be found in the room is a chair at the foot of the bed.

Each of the long walls on either side of the room is sparse in its decoration.  The same could be said of the wall with the door, which is mostly taken up by the door itself.  To the left of the bed is a door that leads to a bathroom. There is such little space between the door and the bed that the man is immediately in the bathroom upon exiting the bed from that side. On the final narrow wall is the room&#39;s only window. Outside of this window there is a large neon sign which is currently turned off, though it is still hot from the recently excited chemicals within it.  The room is never dark.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;&lt;click &quot;What does the man on the bed look like?&quot;&gt;&gt;&lt;&lt;toggleclass &quot;#protagonistDesc&quot; &quot;hidden&quot;&gt;&gt;&lt;&lt;/click&gt;&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;protagonistDesc&quot; class=&quot;hidden&quot;&gt;His lower body lies half concealed by the sheet while his upper extremities approach the lower limits of the mattress.  Both are covered in dozens of what one might call poorly poorly executed tattoo work.  &lt;img src=&quot;C:\Users\cjkoa\Google Drive\cjko.ART\cjko.Twine\Infinite Slice\images\chapter 1\player_inBed.png&quot; width=&quot;300px&quot; hspace=&quot;20&quot; vspace=&quot;20&quot; align=&quot;right&quot;&gt;

His head hangs slightly off the edge. &lt;/div&gt;\

Momentarily, the man will be stirred from sleep by the sunlight on his face.  When that moment arrives there will be a transient flash of confusion as his mind catches up to the bright, loud, sensuous stimuli of waking life. Soon after, he will become cognizant that he has returned to his bedroom.



