&quot;Forget the delivery was coming today? Again?&quot; The Chooch asks.

$name briefly smiles as he decides whether or not to lie to the jolly fellow standing before him. After a second, he opts to not humor The Chooch with trifling excuses.

&quot;I may have completely forgotten,&quot; $name sighs, still grinning. &quot;I feel like you were just here yesterday.&quot;

&quot;Where does the time go? Where does it come from for that matter? Give me a hand, yeah?&quot;

$name takes the crate of goods from the delivery man and stows them inside before returning to the alley.  When he returns The Chooch has lit a cigarette and is taking a leisurely break on a nearby crate and looking at the curvature of the horizon. $name takes a seat next to him, deeming it appropriate to postpone his trip to the market.

&lt;&lt;click &quot;Decribe &#39;The Chooch&#39;.&quot;&gt;&gt;&lt;&lt;toggleclass &quot;#theChoochDesc1&quot; &quot;hidden&quot;&gt;&gt;&lt;&lt;/click&gt;&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;theChoochDesc1&quot; class=&quot;hidden&quot;&gt;A crate of various produce and cheese in tot, The Chooch is an unthreatening character wearing a backwards cap. $name His clothes mismatched, his wit unmatched, The Chooch ellicits chuckles from the coldest individuals. 

In tandem with his goofy demeanor, The Chooch harbors an inner wisdom that is highly regarded within the circles he runs in.  Though $name couldn&#39;t always take his sagely advice to heart (nor seriously), he could always appreciate the kind and clever manners in which it was delivered. For its humorous quality or absurd exposition was sublime and almost artistic in nature.&lt;/div&gt;\

For a moment both said nothing. Pleasant weather and comfortable company allowed $name to [[let his mind wander.]]



